data.name: AlertBox7.Text
data.value: This alert dialog only appears when modifying resources of a PE file (*.dll, *.exe, ...) that is part of the Windows system. If the PE file is not located in any subfolder of %windir%, modifications will be automatically made without remembering these preferences and without displaying the alert dialog

data.name: alertBox24.Text
data.value: It is a service that monitors Windows events and plays sounds based on the received events. It serves as a deflection method for charger connection/disconnection sounds (compatible with any version of Windows) and logoff, logon, lock, unlock, and shutdown sounds (in Windows 8 and higher).
